sentence: Susan Wojcicki, a member of the board of directors at Salesforce.com ( CRM ), bought 1,353 shares of the company's common stock on Jan. 9.
At $73.86 per share, she paid a total of $99,932.58 for the new shares.
IK-> The technicals for CRM ($75.40 up $1.27) are neutral with an upward trend.
The stock has support around $71.86 and recent resistance has been around $76.55.
Look at the Feb. 67.50/62.50 bull-put spread for a 25-cent credit or better.
That's an 5.3% return and the stock has to fall 10.5% to cause a problem.
